					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Do you mean you're using a maximum-sized 8 KB quad tilemap, and trying to DMA <em>that</em> into VRAM in one shot?  Yeah, that's not going to fly without letterboxing.<br /><br />Like tepples says, what most games did was update rows and columns as they scrolled into view.  Since the screen is only 224 lines high, you don't actually need more than two &quot;screens&quot; worth of tilemap in VRAM for seamless scrolling if you do it right.  Look into what $2115 does, and maybe take a second look at $2107-210A if you don't already know how to make the map smaller.</div>

					
